
[1]transportation

   TRANSPORTA'TION, n. The act of carrying or conveying from one place to
   another, either on beasts or in vehicles, by land or water, or in air.
   Goods in Asia are transported on camels; in Europe and America, either
   on beasts or on carriages or sleds. But transportation by water is the
   great means of commercial intercourse.

   1. Banishment for felony.

   2. Transmission; conveyance.

   3. Transport; ecstasy. [Little used.]

   4. Removal from one country to another; as the transportation of
   plants.
